<div class="center"><br />Luckily, I had a camera to capture Dave attacking on Matt on the climb</div>
<p>After getting swamped with faculty calls, I was unable to go the the screening of <a href="http://www.decliningbydegrees.org/">Declining by Degrees</a>, a PBS documentary about the decline of higher ed in the US.  Fortunately, I own the DVD, so I can watch it tonight in time for the <a href="http://datcjunto.blogspot.com">DATC Junto</a> tomorrow.</p>
<p>Consequently, I <strong>was</strong> able to get out for a ride!  Dave and Matt soldiered up the hill with me.</p>
<p>In spite of the pools of glacial runoff and mounds of sand on the road, conditions were perfect.  The temperature was actually about 10&deg;F warmer up top than down on campus, but winds were blustery up high.</p>
<p>Tomorrow's supposed to be even warmer.  Who knows?!  Maybe the street sweeper will have cleaned up the sand too.</p>